The city of Neura; a place where everyone claimed that justice was for all.
But Luna, a young fox, knew very well that some animals had to work twice as hard as the others.
It was her first day in the Investigation Department.
Suspicious eyes followed her everywhere.
The rhino chief only said:
“Don’t make a mistake. Foxes get one chance—no more.”
By nightfall, the city was shaken by the news:
a peaceful sheep had gone missing…
